The forces of the mega-strike are gathering
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers' Councils will constitute, on Friday, their strike commission which will be in charge of coordinating Monday's indefinite strike.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the law on health funds, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause significant traffic jams because rail traffic will be stopped almost completely and the employees of BKV (public transport company) will also strike until 1pm.
The unions of the league will make known, Friday afternoon, the details of their strike of Monday, organized with the National Association of workers' councils.
The strike commission of LIGA - MOSZ will also be constituted, it will serve as coordinator of the actions of Monday.
On Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and, from Monday, the organizations joining the strike will stop work for an indefinite period if they fail to reach an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the law on health insurance funds, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not adopt the law on health funds, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for strike action.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide what to do next.
According to Monday's agenda of the national assembly, it is likely that the vote on the law on health funds will take place only late at night, or even at night.
Due to the strike scheduled for Monday, significant traffic jams are expected: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of public transport in Budapest and more than half of Volán companies are at risk of being stopped.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the road will also be blocked.
Many unions and civil organizations have joined the call for a strike, the list of which is constantly updated on the League's website.
Some organizations report going on strike for an indefinite period, others have declared a temporary stoppage of work.
Until Thursday afternoon the M<0xC3><0x81>V (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) have not been able to find an agreement on the minimum services, but, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people are taking the train.
According to current communications, the Budapest public transport will strike from the start of service until 1pm, the Budapest airport between 7am and 9am, the Industrial Trade Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will strike for four hours, the Teachers' Union and the Democratic Teachers' Union have called for a strike for 2 hours and 2 hours respectively.
The National Association of Physicians will go on strike throughout the country alternately, the Syndicat des employés de la santé et du secteur social (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will go on a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands, formulated by the League, demands that the government withdraw its proposal on health reform and submit a new conception to social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating the pension to be implemented from next year is introduced in several stages.
The third claim is for a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, which would make it possible to transfer into the system the functions that deserve it before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), attached to the Trade Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning secondary railway lines and the expectation of another proposal.
Political Capital: the Hungarian Guard has increased the country risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital (Risk Analysis Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August, with the support of the Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increases, in several aspects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its “Risk Warning”, the company points out that, in connection with the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that “in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes may occur as a result of the aggravation of the already existing ethnic tension between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population of Hungary”.
The research institute added that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard likely aimed at provoking this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groups that have based a political strategy on the dispute between Gypsies and Hungarians".
The problem is compounded, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are reinforced and aggressive conflict is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the effect of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the activity of the Hungarian Guard "has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to confidence in the stability and democratic maturity of the country".
They recall that, as a result of increased publicity given to the reorganisation of radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary since the autumn of 2006, numerous associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007 calling themselves the "national association for self-defence".
“The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civil organization while they publicly declare the preparation of their adherents for defense missions (catastrophes, national defense, defense of order), armed if necessary, moreover, evoking the incapacity of the police, the army, in other words of the state,” they added.
They pointed out that everything was going according to the method that, based on the rancour of the political society and the parties, seeks to disguise different political ambitions under a civil aspect.
The emphasis on civil character and association status thus serves only to avoid the legal pitfalls of registering these associations with the court but they also constitute a political strategy.
The analysis indicates that the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a factor that also increases the risk in relation to neighbourly relations.
“In recent months, many neighbouring countries have cited the Hungarian Guard as a potential source of risk and ultra-nationalist political actors in some neighbouring countries wish to justify their anti-Hungarian policy by referring to the constitution of the Hungarian Guard.
This influences the political stability of the region,” they added.
According to the research institute, the constitution of the Hungarian Guard is not a unique phenomenon in Central Eastern Europe, political risks have increased throughout the region.
As they say, the functioning of the Hungarian Guard resembles, for example, the activity of the Bulgarian National Guard whose constitution was declared by the Bulgarian National Union (BNU) in August 2007.
The numerous Roma riots that broke out in a neighborhood of Sofia (Kraszna Poljana) are the origin of the constitution of the Bulgarian guard.
Taking advantage of these events, BNU decided to set up a guard, saying that the organization's goal is "national self-defense."
According to them, over the past 17 years, the gypsies have “terrorized” Bulgaria, but the state has remained inactive and neutral, recalls Political Capital.
They added that the initiative had sparked lively debates in Bulgarian public opinion.
As they say, the declaration of some Bulgarian Roma organizations regarding the constitution of their own guard as resistance signals the increased risk of ethnic clashes.
The functioning of the Hungarian Guard showing similarities with that of the Bulgarian National Guard does not exclude that Hungarian Roma react to the threat in the same way by organizing their own self-defense, reads the warning of risk of Political Capital.
At the request of the telegraph agency, Attila Juhász, research director of Political Capital, said: Risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he said, their risk analysis is published every year and if events occur that could impact the change in risk, they inform the public, as in this case, by publishing a risk warning.
The party is not marked in red everywhere
In Hungary, the law defines exactly the holidays and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganize the working days whose number will decrease next year.
The holidays are not uniform in the EU and the US either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes between national and state holidays as well as days of rest.
Rest days are often linked to religious festivals or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the New Year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the New Year are also days of rest, the latter all the more so that the New Year's Eve can rest quietly.
In addition, in a year, we have a total of eleven festivals marked in red.
March 15 is a national holiday, in commemoration of the 1848 revolution, as is October 23, which is also the day commemorating the 1956 revolution.
On August 20th, we celebrate the constitution of our state, May 1st is Labor Day and on November 1st and 2nd, we remember our deceased family members and friends.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or even religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, according to the calendar, it has become common to reorganize the working days in cases where there is only one working day left before or after the holiday marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price of extended weekends by working or going to school on the Saturday before the extended weekend.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has ruled in a special regulation on the days of replacement of the days before or after the holidays.
The law extends to all employers and their employees, to civil servants and to persons working in the public service.
It does not apply, however, to service companies, to institutions that operate without interruption and in service, because of their vocation, and also to days of rest.
This year, the working days will be changed only around the end of the year holidays: from December 24, life stops almost all over the country because according to experience the majority of people instead work overtime or take holidays that they have saved for these purposes to be able to spend the days between Christmas and New Year's Day at home.
Next year many holidays fall in the middle or end of the week, therefore there will be fewer changes in the level of working days compared to this year.
The calendar will be reorganized the first time around Labor Day to allow employees to stay at home four days in a row.
Saturday, April 25th will be a working day to have a rest day on Friday, May 2nd.
Another change is planned for October 23rd: Saturday October 18th will be a work day replacing Friday 24th.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year is announced under the sign of the holidays because from December 24, everyone will take a non-stop break even if New Year's Day falls on a Wednesday.
Six Futile Things That Can Hurt Colleagues Terribly
Emails we forget to send, voice messages we never receive, innocent lies that annoy us almost more: these are things that “beautify” the daily life of a workplace.
The question is whether one gets used to these troubles or takes up the challenge and consciously avoids ambiguous situations, causing trouble to others.
Examples.
“Excuse me, I forgot to tell you that you were called from the marketing department,” a colleague tells you.
That you missed a date?
At best he is sorry and tries to fix things by calling the marketing department to tell them that he forgot to pass the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, this is done with an apology.
Before you have painful explanations, it’s helpful to think about how you might cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and make efforts to avoid them.
Borrow something that doesn't belong to you?
There is nothing more annoying than wanting to take a folder, an office tool or the phone and you can’t find them anywhere.
Remember the day before you put the stapler on the desk but it disappeared the next morning?
Do you happen to find your pen that you thought was lost on your colleague's desk?
Don't take anything from your colleagues without asking, or they're right to be mad at you for stealing their property.
Do not bring envelopes, post-it notes in your pocket because it can be annoying that there are no more and you need them right away.
Are you talking about co-workers' privacy?
There are no good ways to stop gossip from spreading.
Who did what, with whom?
Or and why?
Do not tell everyone your information (suppositions) about the privacy of your colleagues!
If a colleague shares his intimate secrets with you, do not abuse his trust!
Bury the shared information in yourself and do not discuss it with your colleagues in his absence even if your colleagues are also aware of it.
Do you call yourself sick for no good reason?
When you call the office and declare yourself sick under the pretext of a heartbreaking headache because you feel bad or feel you need rest that day, think about the fact that your work, your urgent affairs, your future missions must be carried out by someone else in your place.
Don't get your colleagues in trouble!
If you know in advance that you will not go to work the next day or that something may happen that would force you to stay at home, do not forget to notify your boss and your colleagues to avoid that they are surprised by your absence the next day.
Chilling, snickering, phone
Do you immerse yourself in your work but the sneering of your colleagues brutally snatches you away?
Have you unwittingly become a witness to a telephone conversation that you would have been better off not listening to?
Do not disturb your colleagues with humming, chanting, loud discussions (that you lead above their head), beating of feet, big words or discontent expressed out loud.
They can be annoying even if your colleagues are not immersed in a project (writing, design, organization).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
If your work is not done for the set deadline, you forget to send a mail or an important message, do not accuse anyone for this forgetfulness!
Don’t put it on the account of possible chaos in the office or your noisy colleagues!
Recognize it if you have made a mistake and if it has presented disadvantages for others, make up for the mistake!
Ask how you could make up for your mistake, make up for the negligence!
Do you feel too at home in the office?
Putting on a jogging and slippers is comfortable at home but they are not suitable in the office!
Do not wear a comfortable jog even if your function allows it!
Do not be neglected, respect your colleagues and yourself by dressing properly, and if your function requires it by wearing pretty and elegant clothes, to go to work!
