The Bank of England takes note of the concerns by offering 10 billion pounds over five weeks
The Bank of England said on Thursday it was anxious to ease the current return of concerns about credit conditions, and announced an offer of <0xC2><0xA3>10 billion at the base rate of 5.75% over five weeks, an offer of unusual duration.
“To alleviate concerns that financial market conditions will be particularly tight at the end of the year, and to give banks greater certainty in how they will organize their liquidity positions over this period, the Bank intends to offer a significant proportion of its planned supply of reserves during the maintenance period commencing on December 6 in the form of a five-week open market operation,” the bank said in a statement.
The bank says 10 billion pounds (14 billion euros) will be put on the market on December 6 at 12:15 GMT, at the base rate and until January 10.
This appears to be the first time the BoE has placed five-week liquidity on the market in an open market operation.
These are usually done within a week.
The BoE said in a statement that it “stands ready to take further steps to maintain rates” of overnight interbank loans in line with its base rate.
The overnight interbank rate was 5.829% on Wednesday.
The three-month rate was 6.6%, the highest since September 18.
Since the start of the financial crisis in the summer, the sums put on the market by the Bank of England were accompanied by a high penalty rate that had deterred banks from resorting to them.
According to some rumors, corroborated by the evolution of the price of the pound against the euro, many had preferred to subscribe to the sums put on the market by the European Central Bank, at more advantageous rates and with a more assured discretion.
UMP and NC refuse consideration of PS proposals on purchasing power
The UMP and Nouveau Centre groups on Thursday refused to discuss the articles of the socialist bill on purchasing power, which amounts to a rejection of the text.
Listed in a socialist "niche" (meeting at the initiative of a parliamentary group), the text declined a dozen measures adopted Tuesday by the national office of the PS among which the increase of 50% of the premium for employment, the reinstatement of the floating TIPP, a transport check or the supervision of rents.
UMP and NC having voted against the examination of the articles (180 votes against 115), the sitting was adjourned at the end of the general discussion which gave rise to exchanges, sometimes lively, between majority and opposition a few hours before the television intervention of Nicolas Sarkozy on the purchasing power.
The leader of the PS deputies Jean-Marc Ayrault announced that his group will represent all of his proposals in the form of amendments to the amending finance bill considered by the Assembly next week.
A new festival is born
Following many rumors about the creation by C3 Presents of a new music festival in Philadelphia, the promoter/producer announces the Vineland Music Festival in New Jersey, in partnership with Festival Republic of British producer Melvin Benn.
“For our company, it’s an honor to work with a person who has, no less than, inspired the current festival movement in America,” C3’s Charlie Jones told Billboard.com.
C3 produces Chicago’s Lollapalooza Festival and the Austin City Limits Music Festival.
Vineland, New Jersey, is a summer camping destination.
The festival is scheduled to take place Aug. 8-10 on a 500-acre private farm about 40 minutes from Philadelphia.
Formerly known as Mean Fiddler, Festival Republic director Melvin Benn is one of the most respected festival producers in the world.
In 1989, he took the helm of the Reading Festival in the United Kingdom, which annually attracts some 80,000 people.
In 1999, Melvin Benn added the Leeds Festival to his portfolio and, in 2006, Festival Republic created the Latitude Festival in Henham Park, Suffolk.
Since 2002, as co-owner, Melvin Benn has also been in charge of the production, licensing and organisational tasks of the Glastonbury Festival, which can now accommodate up to 177,500 people.
Calling Glastonbury the “most inspiring event” he has ever attended, C3’s Charlie Jones says his company and Melvin Benn’s are working in parallel to give the region a European-style festival-event.
“We had chosen Philadelphia as a market and were working diligently with the Fairmount Parks Commission to create a festival in downtown Philadelphia,” says Charlie Jones.
“We were in talks with the city and the Commission was motivated and excited by this project.
“Unfortunately, we got bogged down in politics because of the current administration,” Jones said.
“Fortunately, we were able to chat with Melvin Benn and we are preparing to create a superb festival on an exceptional site that will ultimately serve the people of Philadelphia.”
C3 Presents revived the Lollapalooza festival in 2005 at Chicago's Grant Park, after standing out in the festival landscape in 2002 with the Austin City Limits Music Festival.
The two events recorded gross revenues of $9.8M and $11.3M in 2007, respectively.
Both festivals are held in urban areas.
“Melvin Benn’s European model is a country festival, while ours are rather urban green spaces,” says Charlie Jones.
The goal is to merge, in one way or another, the two formulas to give both an impression of rural festival to the European and urban to the American.
Vineland is roughly halfway between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
“The community of Vineland, including the mayor, enthusiastically supports this event,” says Charlie Jones.
He declined to disclose the terms of the deal, but said they were "interesting enough to make it possible to invest in such an event and host a festival that, hopefully, will have a long life."
Charlie Jones says that the capacity of this festival is "very large", like that of 80,000 people at the Bonnaroo Music Festival in Tennessee.
He says that invitations have been issued to the groups, but that nothing could yet be confirmed when going to press.
“Vineland will be rock, but the music will be varied, hoping to attract all kinds of spectators,” says Charlie Jones.
His partners on C3, which received the Top Independent Promoter award at the last Billboard Touring Awards, are Charlie Walker and Charles Attal.
