Congress approves transposition of Mifid, which came into force on November 1
In parallel with its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of the Congress on the amendments incorporated in the draft in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts of Members of Parliament and Senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation to ensure the protection of investors and to regulate in detail the activity of the organizations so that the markets function effectively.
The MIFID, which amends the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of the financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will allow financial advisory services to be provided both for specialised corporate purposes and to natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial advisory companies (FACs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to the regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems, which compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate control by the CNMV.
Passing through the Congressional Economics Committee, several amendments were added, including one that highlights that securitized debt will be considered a “complex” financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of high-risk U.S. mortgages (subprime).
In addition, they took advantage of the transposition of the management took the opportunity to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics can have 30 years after in 1977 was approved, the royal decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require the authorization of the CNMV and who will be able to lend its services of marketing products and attracting new customers to different investment companies at the same time.
