What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver against possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that, choosing the right auto insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise takes the form of an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate due to their prudence.
Similarly, using censuses, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use made of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency, the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will show the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when contracting with affordable insurance, such as limited driving experience and seniority of the driver's license.
Although the ideal insurance is all-risk insurance, there are other, more economical options.
The most forward-thinking drivers can opt for any risk insurance with deductible, so that they get the coverage of any risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be," specifies Luis Noguera, the head in Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25 years of age try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
“The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the company’s profit.
If the company has had a good year it can afford to increase the bonuses, "clarifies Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25 it becomes easier for drivers to contract with insurance, since the loss rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to choose an all-risk insurance with franchise.
"Normally young people can not enjoy the experience previously acquired after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at any risk, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claims rate, because the premiums will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with deductible (can be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed driving and they have a greater purchasing power to allow themselves the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises," says Luis Noguera.
For retirees, an all-risk insurance with deductible is preferable (being this one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver against possible claims, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is fundamental to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
