In the 2003 PISA studies, the proportion of students at risk decreased from 29 to 20 per cent.
In total, however, the Saarland has not improved as much as other federal states.
Bavarians are doing better.
And in spite of the Saarland, foreign language proficiency is not measured by PISA studies - one could otherwise earn points in this field.
Because the language of the neighbor is mandatory in high schools - even if the Sarrois are not French.
